Admiral Hipper META.notes: zTENTATIVE. Weak slow, and meh shielding = usually not having +15% dmg

Adventure Galley.notes: Can +1 ammo, but is weak to planes and uses IX-exclusive guns.

Alfredo Oriani.notes: Huge debuff but on special timing.

An Shan.notes: DDG plus some armor break. Buffs An Shan class.

Asashio.notes: Buffs the ships mentioned in the skill.

Asuka.notes: Buffs Senran Kagura ships, likes Senran Kagura ships.

Atago.notes: Augment adds about 69% more damage to a bad ship, making Atago decent now. Nice.

Attilio Regolo.notes: Has barrage with every main gun shot, so use a faster gun like Twin 100mm Kai.

Aurora.notes: Enemy DD/CL only. Taking your fleet's hit rate from 70% to 90% is a 29% buff (a bit less for vanguard).

Avrora.notes: Requires high-DPS vanguard teammates. Has awful stats herself.

Azuma.notes: Generic CB. Similar to Drake in cost and performance, but the rainbow CB gun is event limited.

Baltimore.notes: For CV fleet with multiple USS CVs. Augment is decent and now has a small buff for Kearsarge's FP damage.

Blücher.notes: Was a decent gold-level tank for 2022, but it's now 2025.

Bolzano META.notes: Elite META ship lol. Can tank/AA a little better when solo vanguard, but why would you do that.

Brest.notes: CB with minor healing. Prefers Iris gear for better AA. For damage, just ignore the Iris gear and use FP AA.

Bristol.notes: Lantern relies on RNG in vanguard and boss movement. Average speed vg with middle boss may have 50% success.

Chang Chun.notes: DDG plus faction buffs. Assumed to be buffing some SN or Dragon Empery ships.

Chao Ho.notes: With augment, no longer griefs the fleet's AA. Her DMG, AA, and ASW are still bad though.

Chapayev.notes: Large fleet buff against DDs, and buffs vanguard damage against all.

Cheshire.notes: Portland with good AA. Better than Eugen's, but still really bad damage.

Chien Wu.notes: Typical 2024 gold CA, but worse than lala/carl

Chikuma.notes: Requires an IJN CV and buffs CVs. Weak slow. Additional RNG debuff.

Cleopatra.notes: zTENTATIVE has fleet air damage reduction but not AA carry-level AA.

Cleveland.notes: Do you like 25% chance per salvo?

Columbia.notes: Augment adds about 15% more damage, including the new weak barrage.

Drake.notes: Drek b**. Use Drake's normal Triple 234mm or Unzen's HE Triple 203mm/55.

Duisburg.notes: Only usable in W14 because her summons can block rammers (but not as well as Momo's flowers). They're fragile though.

Edinburgh.notes: Requires AP gun. Armor break is not up enough to be awarded Offense Buff 1.

Eldridge.notes: Consistent slow and RNG massive buff to vanguard survivability. Also a free +10 Hedgehog.

Emden.notes: Buffs KMS FP. Weak slow. Choose between Offense and Defense Buff.

Evertsen.notes: Bad ship and even bad tech!

Fancy.notes: Can +1 ammo, but is weak to planes and uses IX-exclusive guns.

Fargo.notes: Buffs flagship damage but not by enough to be rated. Cargo can draw some enemy fire.

Fei Yuen.notes: Prefers a non-DD Dragon Empery ship.

Fleuret.notes: Buffs Le Hardi class. Do you know who is in Le Hardi class? Me neither.

Forbin.notes: Vanguard fleet is limited to Iris Libre, Vichya Dominion...and Senran Kagura and To Love Ru lmao.

Friedrich Carl.notes: Assume the off-tank has decent FP.

Fu Shun.notes: Squishiest and highest dmg DDG. No help for teammates.

Fubuki.notes: After augment, huge buffs for all DDs. Not tiered as a TRP buffer.

Gallant.notes: The barricades get destroyed so quickly because they're big, so no Defense Buff.

Giosuè Carducci.notes: Bad. Use fast torps. Contradictory skill, requires taking damage while being made of paper.

Gloucester.notes: Offense Buff is only when Out of Ammo.

Glowworm.notes: For ramming memes. Use torpedo that reloads between 20 and 23s like quint mags. Mk IX to be tested.

Golden Hind.notes: Can +1 ammo, but is weak to planes and uses IX-exclusive guns. Buffs MOT ships.

Gorizia.notes: Requires RN 🍕 gear and buffs Zara class or RN 🍕 vanguard.

Guam.notes: CB with amazing AA. Consistent armor break for BB fleets.

Guichen.notes: Can do short timeable freezes if with another FFNF/MNF ship.

Hai Chi.notes: Prefers another Dragon Empery ship. Smokes.

Hai Tien.notes: Prefers another Dragon Empery ship. Can technically be used as a buffer for DDGs

Hai Yung.notes: Purple ship from the 19th century, bad.

Hammann II.notes: ARA for CV fleet. Free ASW. Flagship Cover. Great skills on a terrible vessel.

Haruka Amami.notes: A one-time timeable debuff. Quite late if level 1 without preload.

Helena.notes: Huge Offense Buff averages to 24% timed main fleet damage and 12% vanguard damage.

Helena META.notes: Desynced debuff. Desynced freeze that relies on movement RNG to hit.

Houston II.notes: You've beaten the game. +1 CL FP for you.

Ibuki.notes: TRP fleet damager. Very strong preloaded damage, gets relatively weaker as battle length increases.

Isuzu.notes: Requires life support to be used in Chapter 15.

Jamaica.notes: Requires and buffs any version of Sheffield.

Janus.notes: Buffs DD/CLs, especially J-class. Prefers 2 other HMS ships, especially a J-class.

Jervis.notes: Buffs HMS DDs if with 2 other HMS ships. Prefers fleet of DD/CLs only.

Jintsuu META.notes: TRP buff. TRP fleet damager. 3s invincibility with insane burst damage.

Kala Ideas.notes: CB with gold rarity. Assumed to not be in a fleet with Item Attacks. And the 3s invincibility is hard to time.

Kawakaze.notes: Uses cheap blue Single 76mm. Or expensive Single 113mm. Buffs IJN DD damage against cruisers.

Kawakaze META.notes: zTENTATIVE - requires blood shadows to stay alive to exceed Plymouth in DPS. If they die fast, still better than normal Kawakaze.

Kazagumo.notes: ARA for CV fleet. Great for Shinano, but that's not assumed here.

Kent.notes: HEY Shikikan! Do you like 25% chance per salvo?

Kirov META.notes: One-time 15% debuff. Desynced slows. Great for EX if you left her at level 1 for some reason.

L'Audacieux.notes: Buffs DDs, especially FFNF/MNF DDs. Requires another FFNF/MNF ship. Worse in short battles.

Laffey II.notes: AA debuff. Very tanky, especially against fewer high-damage hits.

Lala Satalin Deviluke.notes: Discount black hole on AoA, and minor air buff. Drake sidegrade otherwise.

Le Mars.notes: Vanguard fleet is limited to Iris Libre, Vichya Dominion...and Senran Kagura and To Love Ru lmao.

Le Triomphant.notes: Please do not use as main tank.

Lila Decyrus.notes: Requires another Atelier ship to generate enough AP for her.

Little Anchorage.notes: How dare I say she's a bad ship

Little Cheshire.notes: Requires life support to be used in Chapter 15.

Little Ägir.notes: 15% slow that is somewhat but inconsistently timeable due to CB gun angles.

Matchless.notes: TRP buff. 61% chance for a Quint Torp, assuming 100% hit rate. Needs at least LB2, level 30.

Memphis META.notes: Weak slow. Defense buff for some META ships.

Miller.notes: Very bad tankiness but needs to main tank for minor buffs. All she has Carrier Escort, which doesn't even proc immediately.

Misaki.notes: Buffs DOA ships and prefers another DOA ship.

Mogador.notes: Buffs torps/TBs. Desynced and very short freeze.

Momo Belia Deviluke.notes: Extremely consistently blocks ramming ships. Delayed 25% slow x2 on AoA. Can use Plymouth gun or Single 150mm.

Musketeer.notes: Needs a long time to ramp up her Damage.

Nana Astar Deviluke.notes: Uses cheap blue Single 76mm or expensive Single 113mm. Great mob damage but whiffs against moving bosses.

Napoli.notes: CB with CA hull type. Smokes for herself very well, making her the tankiest vanguard ship in general.

Nicholas.notes: How many RNG skills can you fit on a ship?

Northampton II.notes: Slow for CV fleet with a USS CV flagship.

Noshiro μ.notes: TRP buff. Works with submarines too.

Ognevoy.notes: Tiny heal. Don't expect her to chain barrages against high-level enemies.

Pittsburgh.notes: Consistent armor break for BBs. Ideally flagship fires first.

Pola.notes: Requires another RN 🍕 ship. Buffs RN 🍕 vanguard, especially Zara class.

Portsmouth Adventure.notes: Can +1 ammo, but is weak to planes and uses IX-exclusive guns.

Princess Hime.notes: She carries not-so-big cargo. Buffs SSSS (the collab faction) ships.

Prinz Adalbert.notes: Was a decent gold-level tank for 2022, but it's now 2025.

Prinz Eugen.notes: All tank but extremely poor damage.

Prinz Eugen μ.notes: Buffs vanguard damage, and prefers a muse ship.

Prinz Heinrich.notes: Was a decent gold-level tank for 2021-2022, but it's now 2025.

Regensburg.notes: Requires another KMS ship. Desynced buff for KMS.

Reisalin Stout.notes: Can ignore buffs for Atelier ships. Stronger in shorter battles. Uses special gear.

Ritsuko Akizuki.notes: Buffs Idolmaster ships or other ships with her equipped cargo.

Roon.notes: Augment is huge, avg +30% FP over 80s, barrage, +5% dmg, about 10%/10%/30% main gun mod multiplicative increase.

Roon μ.notes: Desynced freeze and debuff relies on movement RNG to hit.

Saint Louis.notes: Requires HE gun. Augment is huge, +15% main gun, ok barrage, another +10% all dmg, another +15% to L/M.

San Diego.notes: No. 1 AA. Her augment barrage is bugged and will probably never be fixed, but her damage is still high.

San Francisco.notes: Read her skills. The bonus columns do not all apply simultaneously.

Santa Fe.notes: Decent DPS, and Flares are nichely huge debuff but on special timing.

Scylla.notes: Time her torpedoes with carrier airstrikes.

Sendai.notes: Huge debuff but on special timing. Also buffs DD/CL torps.

Sheffield.notes: Extremely strong augment, ~75% more damage. But still a bad ship.

Shimakaze.notes: TRP fleet damager. Uses cheap blue Single 76mm. Or expensive Single 113mm.

Shimanto.notes: Does a bit of everything and can stop your main fleet from burning too long.

Shiranui.notes: Very rarely drops collectible trophy boxes.

Sirius.notes: Requires multiple carriers. Buffs carriers, especially against DD, CL, and CA.

Suzunami.notes: Timeable slow on torpedo hit is weaker than Aegir's, but Suzunami has much higher hit chance.

Swiftsure.notes: Around 50% uptime on a decent debuff. Use a gun with high shells per second, like 6 shells in 3 seconds.

Tai Yuan.notes: DDG plus some shields. Requires full fleet.

Tanikaze.notes: TRP buff. 61% chance for a Quint Torp, assuming 100% hit rate. Needs at least LB2, level 55.

Tashkent.notes: Buffs SN DDs and has a weak slow. Not assumed, but could pair with Nakhimov.

Trafalgar.notes: zTENTATIVE Single 113 >= Single 76 >= 100 kai. Timed EVA Rate debuff, perma 15% slow. Requires flagship with main gun.

Trieste.notes: Huge debuff but on special timing.

Trinidad.notes: Pretty good dps actually, a third of it being from the 15s barrage. But just below the threshold for a 2.

Voroshilov.notes: Tankiness requires enemy planes. Weak slow and small FP buff. Explicitly say that she's not assumed to be with Nakhi.

Watarase.notes: Requires IJN flagship. Damage depends on the reload time of the flagship.

Wichita META.notes: Pure GLASS cannon who can pull crazy numbers if the stars align to keep her alive long enough at low HP.

Yat Sen.notes: Requires and buffs DE ships. Requires her special aux. Not with Ping Hai or Ning Hai (see other row).
Requires and buffs DE ships. Requires her special aux. HUGE buff to Ping Hai or Ning Hai.

Ying Swei.notes: With augment, no longer griefs the fleet's AA. Her DMG and AA are still bad though.

Yuubari.notes: Augment: smoke, shield, and shit ton of barrages. Almost doubles her damage, but still below 2 in Dmg.

Z1.notes: Assumed to be buffing a full Z fleet.

Z28.notes: Requires and buffs Z class. Smokes.

Z47.notes: Uses cheap blue Single 76mm. Or expensive Single 113mm.

Z52.notes: Single 113 >= Single 76 >= 100 kai. FlagshipCover. Slash. Heal lowest by 6%. Fleet buff almost 5%.

Zara.notes: Very minor buff for Zara class.

Ägir.notes: Tank with armor break for any boss and inconsistent slow.

Émile Bertin.notes: Requires DD fleet. Buffs FFNF or MNF DDs.
